headline: DoorDash (NASDAQ:DASH) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: On-demand food delivery service DoorDash (NYSE:DASH) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 37.7% year on year to $3.96 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.48 per share was 17.7% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: DoorDash stock dropping after delivery app misses Q4 estimates
summary: DoorDash (DASH) stock is hitting a speed bump in Wednesday's extended hours trading after the delivery service app reported fourth quarter adjusted earnings ($0.48 per share vs. estimates of $0.55) and revenue results ($3.96 billion vs. estimates of $4.0 billion) that fell shy of Wall Street estimates. Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma joins Market Domination Overtime Host Josh Lipton to help break down the earnings release and the stock's negative response. headline: DoorDash sees strong quarterly growth in sales and orders but warns of big costs
summary: DoorDash said Wednesday its revenue rose 38% in the fourth quarter as it gained new U.S. customers and added new services like restaurant reservations.  DoorDash said its expects adjusted pretax earnings between $675 million and $775 million in the first quarter, which was lower than the $800.6 million Wall Street was expecting, according to analysts polled by FactSet.  DoorDash's stock fell 3% in after-hours trading Wednesday.

summary: DoorDash’s fair value estimate has been trimmed slightly from US$276.39 to US$274.69, with its discount rate reduced modestly from 8.40% to 8.32% and revenue growth assumptions revised up from 24.01% to 24.24%. This reflects a blend of enthusiasm around the company’s long term growth plans and execution, alongside caution from research that questions how profit trajectories and cost timing will play out.
